  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Proposed an  Electricity Transmission Expansion and Supply Improvement Project  is critical for reliability of Energy supply in Nepal and its capacity for power import and export across the border. This Project will address the following three key areas as inputs:(i) Electricity transmission capacity supply expansion including facilitation of increased cross-border power flows which include 2nd  circuit string ig Kohalpur- Mahendranagar 132kV transmission line, construction of Tamakoshi (Khimthi)- Kathmandu 220 kV/400kv transmission line and  expansion of Chapali grid subststion;(ii) Strengthning of the distribution  system in both DCS (East) and DCS (West) and along the Tamakoshi (Khimthi)- Kathmandu  transmission line;(iii) Rehabilitation of Tinau (1 MW) and Sundarijal (640) small- hydro power plants"
    },
    "ne": null
  },
